	"description": "A footer is the last element on the page. At a minimum it is at the bottom of\nthe viewport, or lower if the page content is taller than the viewport. Simple,\nright? ?\n\nWhen working with dynamic content that includes a footer, a problem sometimes\noccurs where the content on a page is not enough to fill it. The footer, rather\nthan staying at the bottom of the page where we would want it to stay, rises up\nand leaves a blank space beneath it.\n\nFor a quick fix, you can absolutely position the footer ",
